title: For Sale:  Remington 1908 Model 10
postcontent: This is a nice Remington Model 10 shotgun from the early 1900's and still shots excellent. This was Remington's answer to the Winchester Model 12 Trench shotgun used in both world wars. 22" original configuration barrel. A couple of things that are unique about the model 10 include the loading and ejection port are one in the same, thus no side ports. The other thing is that this is a breakdown shotgun meaning that it is just like most other breakdown weapons in that it twists apart 90 degrees and the entire front magazine and barrel separate from the receiver. This is the original high capacity home defense shotgun! 615 934 zero 347
